<p>First take a look at your Docker environment:
To see the images downloaded to you system run:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>    ~<span class="nv">$ </span>docker images <span class="o">(</span>There should be none<span class="o">)</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Very minimal example of a Docker container:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>    ~<span class="nv">$ </span>docker run hello-world
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Now run the <code class="highlighter-rouge">docker images</code> command again, you should see that it automatically downloaded the necessary image.</p>

